*****
[2]
Date: Mon 24 Feb 2020 6:00 AM IST
Source: The Times of India (TOI), Times News Network (TNN) [edited]
https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/kolkata/anthrax-ruled-out-as-cause-of-4-rhino-deaths/articleshow/74274885.cms


The forest department has ruled out anthrax as the cause of 4 rhino deaths at Jaldapara National Park last week. "We sent viscera samples to Beigachhira and a private lab. The results were negative for anthrax," a senior forester said.

The department has, however, stopped elephant safaris in the park 'until [Thu 27 Feb 2020] to keep a watch on kunki elephants vaccinated over fears of an anthrax outbreak.

"The department needs to identify the disease and take measures at the earliest," said environmentalist Shyama Prasad Pandey of the Society for Protecting Ophiofauna and Animal Rights.

[Byline: Pinak Priya Bhattacharya]

