[A confusion of results. The latter report has detail in a respected newspaper, and the former has the authority of a national newspaper. And if it was negative, it was for 4 of 5 rhino which leaves the 5th awaiting clarification. And to diagnose anthrax one only needs blood swabs, not viscera. Long ago in the Canadian Northwest Territories we learned that a blood swab was a reliable sample. If you sent blood and it took more than 3 days to arrive and begin being cultured, it would be negative because of decomposition and acidification of the sample. I am sure there will be further reports clarifying what the truth is. - Mod.MHJ

